==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From {{ARchar|[[ارتمض]]}} ({{Unicode|artámaɖa}}), ‘to be consumed by grief and sorrow.’ Cf. {{ARchar|[[رمض]]}} ({{Unicode|rámaɖ}}), ‘parchedness,’ ‘scorchedness’; and {{ARchar|[[رمضاء]]}} ({{Unicode|ramɖá:’}}), ‘sun-baked ground.’

*''Month of the Year:'' '''{{ARchar|رمضان}}'''
**'''Previous:''' {{ARchar|[[شعبان]]}}
**'''Next:''' {{ARchar|[[شوال]]}}

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|رَمَضَانُ}}''' {{IPAchar|(ramaɖá:n)}} {{m}}

#[[Ramadan]], a time of [[fasting]] and the ninth of the twelve months of the Muslim lunar calendar, each beginning with a [[new moon]].

